article.headline: Wright St. 67, Youngstown St. 54
article.story: DAYTON, Ohio -- Troy Tabler scored 24 points to lead Wright State to a 67-54 win over Youngstown State on Saturday night. Tabler was a perfect 10-for-10 from the free-throw line for the Raiders (5-2, 2-0 Horizon League), while Todd Brown chipped in with 15 points and eight rebounds. A 3-pointer from Youngstown State's Vance Cooksey cut the Raiders' lead to two points midway through the second half, but two unanswered 3-pointers from Tabler and Ronnie Thomas pushed Wright State's lead to 48-40 with 9:22 remaining. The Penguins (3-5, 0-2) would get no closer than within five points, as Wright State ended the game with an 8-2 run. Sirlester Martin led Youngstown State with 16 points, nine rebounds and three blocks. The Penguins have now lost three straight. The Raiders shot only 36.5 percent from the field (19-for-52), but scored 24 points off Youngstown State's 23 turnovers.
